Eighteen (85.7%) of the 21 calves were infected with at least one infectious agent of BRD. Among the positive animals, mixed infections were more frequent (13/18; 72.2%) than single infections (5/18; 27.7%) (Table 2
). Single infections were more frequently associated with bacteria (4/18, 22.2%) than with viruses (1/18, 5.5%). Associations between viruses and bacteria were the most frequent 10/18 (55.5%). Other mixed infections presented a frequency of 3/18 (16.6%) (Table 3
).
